3Cp%3ESetting%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20up%20with%20the%20F-method%20can%20mean%20a%20break%20from%20traditional%20formats%2C%20such%20as%20listing%20your%20work%20experience%20in%20reverse%20chronological%20order%2C%20which%20may%20surprise%20some.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Woodrow%20said%20floating%20the%20most%20important%20ideas%20to%20the%20top%20makes%20sense%20if%2C%20for%20example%2C%20your%20most%20relevant%20experience%20for%20a%20job%20isn't%20tied%20to%20your%20latest%20role.%20Or%2C%20in%20other%20cases%2C%20he%20said%2C%20a%20job%20posting%20might%20call%20for%20someone%20with%20a%20master's%20degree%20or%20a%20Ph.D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhy%20would%20you%20put%20it%20lower%20down%20on%20page%20two%20or%20three%3F%20You'd%20want%20it%20on%20page%20one%20somewhere%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0highlighting%20it%20in%20that%20area%20which%20is%20in%20the%20'F%2C'%26quot%3B%20Woodrow%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20any%20case%2C%20he%20said%2C%20it's%20important%20to%20keep%20the%20most%20relevant%20information%20on%20the%20first%20page%20of%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f1748ea1-bb74-4f79-a0e0-dc55bec98a68%5C%22%3EHave%20a%20few%20goals%20in%20mind%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWoodrow%20said%20one%20goal%20for%20your%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20should%20be%20ensuring%20it%20can%20be%20easily%20read%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fats-resume-how-to-build-templates-dream-job-2020-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapplicant-tracking%20software%3C%2Fa%3E%20companies%20often%20use%20to%20sift%20through%20job%20applications.%20Another%20aim%20should%20be%20having%20clear%20section%20titles%20so%20the%20document%20is%20a%20breeze%20for%20a%20recruiter%20to%20navigate.%20Highlight%20things%20like%20relevant%20job%20experience%20for%20a%20role%20you're%20going%20for%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%2C%20Woodrow%20said%2C%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20needs%20to%20influence%20a%20decision-maker%20by%20giving%20proof%20of%20your%20accomplishments.%20He%20recommends%20including%20three%20brief%20examples%20on%20the%20first%20page%20about%20how%20you%20solved%20a%20problem.%20To%20do%20this%2C%20describe%20a%20situation%2C%20give%20context%2C%20and%20use%20metrics%20from%20the%20business%2C%20if%20possible%2C%20to%20demonstrate%20how%20you%20improved%20a%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20an%20abbreviated%20version%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-ace-the-interview-2012-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESTAR%20technique%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20sometimes%20used%20in%20interviewing%2C%20and%20involves%20describing%20a%20situation%20or%20task%2C%20actions%2C%20and%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKyle%20Samuels%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20the%20executive%20search%20firm%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hirecte.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECreative%20Talent%20Endeavors%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20using%20the%20F-method%20to%20lay%20out%20a%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%20can%20make%20sense%20for%20technical%20roles%20where%20a%20recruiter%20needs%20to%20know%20you%20have%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20experience%20with%2C%20say%2C%20a%20particular%20programming%20language%20or%20modeling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20other%20cases%2C%20where%20a%20job%20might%20be%20more%20senior%2C%20artificial%20intelligence%20tools%20that%20do%20a%20first%20pass%20on%20a%20stack%20of%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20might%20make%20the%20F%20idea%20somewhat%20moot%20because%20AI%20bots%20can%20scoop%20up%20huge%20volumes%20of%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20kind%20of%20feels%20like%20a%20poor%20man's%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20Samuels%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20F-method.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20with%20a%20role%20like%20a%20VP%20of%20marketing%2C%20you%20might%20have%20several%20candidates%20who%20would%20be%20a%20great%20fit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20expecting%20to%20see%20the%20exact%20same%20formatting%20or%20ski