3E%3Cp%3EHenley%20%26amp%3B%20Partners%20estimated%20that%20about%20122%2C000%20millionaires%20migrated%20to%20a%20new%20country%20in%202023%2C%20either%20for%20citizenship%20or%20residency.%20While%20the%20US%20is%20home%20to%2037%25%20of%20all%20people%20with%20%241%20million%20in%20liquid%20investable%20assets%2C%20Australia%20topped%20the%20list%20of%20countries%20with%20the%20highest%20net%20inflow%20of%20millionaires.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-cities-most-millionaires-ranking-henley-partners-list-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emillionaires%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202023%20was%20up%2045%25%20from%202022%20and%20is%20the%20highest%20on%20record%20since%20Henley%20%26amp%3B%20Partners%20started%20tracking%20the%20data%20in%202013.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Henley%20%26amp%3B%20Partners%20calculations%2C%20based%20on%20data%20from%20the%20first%20six%20months%20of%202023%2C%20Australia%20was%20expected%20to%20gain%205%2C200%20more%20millionaires%20than%20they%20lost%20from%20the%20previous%20year.%20That%20was%20more%20than%20double%20the%20US%2C%20which%20grew%20by%202%2C100%20HNWIs%20and%20ranked%20fourth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20other%20end%2C%20China%20was%20on%20pace%20to%20lose%20the%20most%20millionaires%20for%20the%20second%20year%20in%20a%20row%2C%20with%20a%20net%20drop%20of%2013%2C500.%20That%20was%20more%20than%20twice%20as%20much%20as%20the%20next%20country%2C%20India%2C%20which%20had%206%2C500%20fewer%20millionaires%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%20The%20UK%20was%20third%20with%20a%20loss%20of%203%2C200.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%20is%20a%20look%20at%20the%20countries%20seeing%20the%20biggest%20net%20inflow%20of%20millionaires%20and%20why%20they%20chose%20those%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1.%20Australia%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Sydney%20Opera%20House%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F