3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20Family%20Infected%20With%20Brain%20Worms%20After%20Eating%20Undercooked%20Bear%20Meat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAn%20American%20family%20that%20shared%20a%20meal%20of%20bear%20meat%20at%20a%20gathering%20was%20infected%20with%20brain%20worms%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fwww.cdc.gov%2Fmmwr%2Fvolumes%2F73%2Fwr%2Fmm7320a2.htm%3Fs_cid%3Dmm7320a2_w%C2%A0%5C%22%3Enew%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20Centers%20for%20Disease%20Control%20and%20Prevention%20(CDC)%20has%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Minnesota%20Department%20of%20Health%20in%202022%20learnt%20about%20a%20man%20hospitalised%20multiple%20times%20within%20a%20short%20period%20after%20showing%20symptoms%20such%20as%20fever%2C%20severe%20muscle%20soreness%2C%20swelling%20around%20the%20eyes%2C%20and%20other%20troubling%20health%20issues.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20further%20investigation%2C%20it%20came%20to%20light%20that%20the%2029-year-old%20had%20attended%20a%20family%20gathering%20in%20South%20Dakota%20before%20he%20took%20sick.%20At%20this%20gathering%2C%20one%20of%20the%20meals%20included%20kabobs%20made%20from%20black%20bear%20meat%20sourced%20from%20northern%20Saskatchewan%20by%20a%20family%20member.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20CDC%20report%2C%20the%20meat%20had%20been%20stored%20in%20a%20freezer%20for%20a%20month%20and%20a%20half%20before%20being%20thawed%20out%20and%20was%20initially%20served%20rare%2C%20due%20to%20its%20darker%20colour.%20Family%20members%20noticed%20the%20undercooked%20taste%20and%20recooked%20it%20before%20serving%20again.%20The%20bear%20meat%20was%20eaten%20by%20nine%20family%20members%20in%20total.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2029-year-old%20man%20got%20severely%20sick%20and%20had%20to%20be%20taken%20to%20the%20hospital%20where%20doctors%20found%20he%20had%20a%20rare%20kind%20of%20roundworm%20called%20trichinellosis%2C%20which%20usually%20comes%20from%20eating%20wild%20animals.%20This%20worm%20can%20travel%20through%20the%20body%20and%20even%20reach%20the%20brain.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Celine%20Gounder%20explained%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Fbrain-worms-rfk-jr-had-are-real-common-doctor-explains%2F%C2%A0%5C%22%3ECBS%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20symptoms%20of%20brain%20worm%20infection%20may%20include%20nausea%2C%20vomiting%2C%20headaches%20and%20seizures.%20However%2C%20some%20may%20not%20experience%20any%20symptoms%20at%20all.%20Dr%20Gounder%20noted%20that%20typically%2C%20the%20immune%20system%20surrounds%20the%20parasites%20and%20turns%20them%20into%20hard%2C%20calcified%20structures%2C%20which%20prevents%20them%20from%20spreading%20further%20in%20the%20body.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20CDC%2C%20the%20best%20way%20to%20ensure%20these%20parasites%20are%20killed%20is%20by%20cooking%20the%20meat%20properly%C2%A0at%2C%20at%20least%20165%C2%A0degree%C2%A0Fahrenheit.%20They%20also%20warned%20the%20parasites%20could%20spread%20to%20other%20foods%2C%20advising%20to%20avoid%20cross-contamination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFive%20other%20family%20members%2C%20including%20a%2012-year-old%20girl%2C%20were%20also%20diagnosed%20with%20freeze-resistant%20worms.%20They%20were%20treated%20with%20a%20medicine%20called%20albendazole%2C%20which%20stops%20the%20worms%20from%20absorbing%20energy%2C%20ultimately%20killing%20them.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716626640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2Frv8fkovo_bear_625x300_25_May_24.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-family-infected-with-brain-worms-after-consuming-undercooked-bear-meat-5741925%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22They%20were%20treated%20with%20a%20medicine%20called%20albendazole%2C%20which%20stops%20the%20worms%20from%20absorbing%20energy%2C%20ultimately%20killing%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2