3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20his%20full%20journey%20isn't%20revealed%2C%20the%20man%20eventually%20found%20himself%20recovering%20from%20cancer%20treatment%20while%20homeless%20on%20the%20streets%20of%20London.%20Wearing%20handouts%20of%20donated%20clothing%2C%20he%20kept%20warm%20one%20winter%20in%20a%20fleece%20that%20-%20he%20reports%20without%20apparent%20bitterness%20-%20came%20emblazoned%20with%20the%20name%20of%20his%20former%20employer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20one%20of%20the%20compelling%20stories%20told%20at%20the%20new%20museum%2C%20which%20opens%20Friday%2C%20founded%20as%20a%20roving%20project%20a%20decade%20ago%20but%20now%20settling%20into%20its%20first%20permanent%20site%20in%20an%20Edwardian%20groundsman's%20lodge%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20North%20London's%20Finsbury%20Park.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20museum's%20opening%20is%20timely%20to%20say%20the%20least.%20Across%20the%20UK%20290%2C000%20households%20sought%20help%20for%20homelessness%20in%202022%2C%20the%20most%20recent%20data%20show%2C%20with%20the%20number%20of%20people%20placed%20in%20temporary%20accommodation%20having%20doubled%20over%20the%20preceding%20decade.%20Many%20people%20still%20can't%20access%20help%2C%20and%20the%20number%20of%20people%20sleeping%20rough%20on%20Britain's%20streets%20rose%2026%25%20in%20the%20same%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20rents%20rising%20faster%20than%20core%20inflation%20and%20an%20acute%20cost%20of%20living%20crisis%20only%20just%20showing%20signs%20of%20abating%2C%20things%20are%20only%20getting%20worse.%20In%20the%20final%20three%20months%20of%202023%20alone%2C%20the%20number%20of%20people%20being%20made%20homeless%20rose%2016%25%20nationwide.%20The%20people%20whose%20experiences%20this%20museum%20explores%20are%20not%20only%20misunderstood%20and%20frequently%20overlooked%2C%20but%20they%20are%20becoming%20more%20statistically%20significant%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOffering%20a%20blend%20of%20storytelling%2C%20education%20and%20advocacy%20focused%20on%20the%20experiences%20of%20homeless%20people%2C%20the%20museum's%20unconventional%20setup%20goes%20beyond%20its%20subject%20alone.%20Rather%20than%20a%20collection%20of%20items%20in%20glass%20cases%2C%20it%20offers%20an%20interactive%20experience%20where%20volunteers%20share%20the%20stories%20behind%20the%20objects%20in%20its%20collection%20-%20all%20amassed%20through%20donations%20from%20their%20homeless%20former%20owners%20-%20to%20small%20groups%20of%20visitors%2C%20using%20the%20exact%20words%20of%20its%20former%20keepers.%20The%20result%20is%20not%20just%20a%20powerful%2C%20humane%20insight%20into%20homeless%20people's%20experiences%20but%20also%20-%20with%20its%20collection%20including%20objects%20as%20mundane%20as%20shopping%20carts%20and%20plastic%20bags%20-%20a%20challenge%20to%20received%20ideas%20of%20what%20museums%20should%20display.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20objects%20included%20in%20the%20museum's%20first%20exhibition%20possess%20meanings%20that%20belie%20their%20modest%20appearance.%20Each%20object's%20narrator%20reveals%20a%20striking%20backstory%3A%20A%20rough%2C%20handled%20wooden%20staff%20repaired%20with%20duct%20tape%2C%20for%20example%2C%20was%20actually%20grabbed%20as%20an%20impromptu%20replacement%20for%20crutches%20that%20a%20homeless%20sufferer%20of%20chronic%20back%20pain%20had%20left%20on%20the%20bus.%20Left%20scarcely%20able%20to%20walk%20on%20the%20curbside%2C%20the%20stick's%20former%20owner%20found%20a%20piece%20of%20discarded%20coppiced%20wood%20in%20a%20front%20garden%2C%20and%20found%20that%20the%20rounded%20bole%20at%20its%20end%20fitted%20his%20hand%20perfectly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomething%20grabbed%20in%20desperation%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20a%20highly%20useful%2C%20even%20reassuring%20piece%20of%20equipment.%20Initially%20grabbed%20as%20a%20stop-gap%20to%20get%20him%20off%20the%20curb%2C%20the%20stick%20became%20something%20its%20new%20owner%20started%20using%20constantly.%20Ultimately%2C%20he%20even%20adorned%20its%20vaguely%20head-shaped%20handle%20with%20a%20glass%20eye%2C%20an%20embellishment%20he%20felt%20showed%20the%20influence%20of%20his%20uncanny%20favorite%20novel%2C%20Iain%20Banks's%20the%20Wasp%20Factory.%20Explored%20more%20closely%2C%20this%20simple%20piece%20of%20wood's%20transition%20from%20waste%20item%20to%20tool%20and%20companion%20shows%20how%20even%20a%20simple%20object%20can%20become%20somebody's%20anchor%2C%20and%20reveals%20sophisticated%20associations%20that%20don't%20fit%20well%20with%20common%20perceptions%20of%20the%20homeless%20as%20lost%20and%20abject.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20stories%20of%20homeless%20people%20as%20admirable%20survivors%20may%20cheer%20visitors%2C%20but%20the%20museum's%20first%20exhibit%20is%20also%20unsettling.%20Working%20on%20the%20cliff%20edge%20on%20which%20many%20Londoners'%20security%20is%20already%20teetering%2C%20the%20museum's%20staff%20see%20the%20people%20whose%20stories%20they%20share%20as%20role%20models%20for%20a%20future%20where%20many%20people's%20lives%20may%20become%20yet%20more%20precarious.%20A%20future%20state%20of%20perma-crisis%2C%20a%20form%20of%20apocalypse%20in%20the%20museum's%20words%2C%20could%20mean%20that%20the%20practices%20keeping%20homeless%20people%20relatively%20safe%20-%20resilience%2C%20mutual%20support%20and%20community%20-%20will%20be%20ever%20more%20indispensable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20flip%20the%20script%20a%20little%20bit%20about%20what%20people%20say%20about%20homelessness%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20the%20museum's%20Operations%20%26amp%3B%20Production%20Manager%20Adam%20Hemmings.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20sensationalism%20and%20pity%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20victim%20narratives%20around%20homelessness.%20What%20we're%20doing%20with%20this%20show%20is%20saying%20actually%20there's%20quite%20a%20lot%20of%20wisdom%2C%20there's%20quite%20a%20lot%20of%20creativity.%20And%20you%20know%2C%20when%20the%20apocalypse%20does%20come%2C%20it%20will%20be%20people%20affected%20by%20these%20issues%20who%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20answers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716626460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-04%2Fb5d41t3_us-homeless_625x300_23_April_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthe-worlds-first-museum-of-homelessness-opens-in-london-5742264%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20stories%20told%20at%20London's%20new%20Museum%20of%20Homelessness%20make%20frighteningly%20clear%20that%20homelessness%20can%20potentially%20happen%20to%20anyone.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthe-worlds-first-museum-of-homelessness-opens-in-london-5742264%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthe-worlds-first-museum-of-homelessness-opens-in-london-5742264%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fthe-worlds-first-museum-of-homelessness-opens-in-london-5742264%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20CEC%20said%20after%20SC's%20decision%20on%20voter%20turnout%20data%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716626457000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-110418192%2Cimgsize-658220.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fwe-will-show-how-people-are-misled-cec-rajiv-kumar-on-scs-verdict-on-voter-turnout-data%2Farticleshow%2F110417998.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Commenting%20on%20the%20recent%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20to%20refrain%20from%20issuing%20directives%20on%20the%20Election%20Commission's%20handling%20of%20Form%2017C%20data%20and%20booth-wise%20voter%20turnout%2C%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20(CEC)%20Rajiv%20Kumar%20emphasized%20the%20need%20to%20dispel%20doubts%20and%20suspicions%20about%20electoral%20processes.%20This%20statement%20was%20made%20after%20he%20cast%20his%20vote%20at%20a%2