90%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ebakery%20refused%20to%20write%20his%20name%20on%20the%20cake.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuch%20situations%20simply%20wouldn't%20occur%20in%20Germany%2C%20as%20a%20name%20like%20that%20would%20be%20rejected.%20The%20reason%20for%20these%20names%20being%20rejected%20is%20due%20to%20child%20protection%20grounds%2C%20as%20they%20are%20seen%20by%20German%20law%20as%20acts%20of%20child%20cruelty.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOther%20names%20that%20have%20been%20rejected%20in%20Germany%20for%20being%20perceived%20as%20too%20cruel%20to%20give%20a%20child%20include%20Satan%2C%20Pepsi-Carola%2C%20Schokominza%20(which%20means%20%26quot%3Bchocolate%20mint%26quot%3B)%2C%20Superman%2C%20and%20Lenin.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFortunately%2C%20this%20particular%20law%20was%20never%20an%20issue%20for%20us%20%E2%80%94%20we%20certainly%20never%20intended%20to%20give%20our%20children%20names%20like%20Stalin%20or%20Captain%20Marvel.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-parent-germany-naming-laws-european-country-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716625861000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664cb37320abc1efe8fbef84%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-parent-germany-naming-laws-european-country-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Germany%20has%20laws%20around%20what%20parents%20can%20name%20their%20kids.%20City%20or%20country%20names%20are%20not%20allowed%2C%20as%20well%20as%20brands%20or%20titles.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Naomi%20Kaye%20Honova)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-parent-germany-naming-laws-european-country-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22