%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20image%20of%20Jess%20Munday.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664b77b214fb5b23cc5e44f4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EDara%20Feller%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20many%20of%20Jess%20Munday's%20San%20Francisco%20friends%20live%20alone.%20But%20Munday%2C%20a%2029-year-old%20who%20works%20in%20tech%20marketing%2C%20was%20able%20to%20swing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20living%20with%20her%20parents%20for%20a%20few%20months%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20during%20which%20time%20she%20saved%20some%20money.%20Then%2C%20she%20struck%20in%20January%202021%20when%2C%20according%20to%20Zillow%2C%20rent%20prices%20in%20the%20city%20were%20the%20lowest%20they've%20been%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20pays%20about%20%242%2C600%20for%20a%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20in%20San%20Francisco's%20Mission%20neighborhood%20and%20makes%20%24175%2C000%20annually.%20It's%20a%20deal%20compared%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.zillow.com%2Frental-manager%2Fmarket-trends%2Fsan-francisco-ca%2F%3Fbedrooms%3D1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedian%3C%2Fa%3E%20rent%20of%20about%20%242%2C900%20for%20a%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20in%20San%20Francisco.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20even%20know%20people%20who%20are%20a%20lot%20older%20than%20me%20who%20are%20living%20with%20roommates%20in%20San%20Francisco%2C%26quot%3B%20Munday%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20thankfully%20in%20a%20financial%20situation%20where%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20do%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2030-something%20American%20dream%20used%20to%20look%20a%20little%20like%20this%3A%20You're%20married%2C%20you%20have%20two%20or%20three%20kids%2C%20and%20you%20own%20your%20starter%20house%20(white%20picket%20fence%20optional).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20things%20have%20shifted.%20Millennials%20are%20getting%20married%20later%2C%20if%20at%20all.%20They're%20having%20kids%20later%2C%20if%20at%20all.%20And%20forget%20owning%20a%20sprawling%20suburban%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20helping%20establish%20a%20new%20millennial%20milestone%20for%20some%3A%20Ditching%20roommates%2C%20moving%20out%20from%20the%20family%20home%2C%20and%20landing%20on%20living%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoing%20solo%20as%20a%20younger%20worker%20has%20become%20increasingly%20popular%20in%20the%20past%20few%20decades%2C%20though%20it's%20still%20relatively%20uncommon%20in%20the%20US.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fdata%2Ftables%2Ftime-series%2Fdemo%2Ffamilies%2Fadults.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECensus%20data%20indicates%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20in%20the%20late%201960s%20and%20early%201970s%2C%20under%203%25%20of%20Americans%20between%2018%20and%2034%20lived%20alone%3B%20by%202023%2C%20that%20number%20had%20tripled.%20Business%20Insider's%20analysis%20of%20American%20Community%20Survey%20microdata%20from%20IPUMS%20found%20that%2010.5%25%20of%20millennials%20lived%20alone%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F9HWsN%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Total%20share%20of%2018%20to%2034-year-olds%20living%20alone%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22413%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EBella%20DePaulo%2C%20a%20social%20scientist%20who%20studies%20single%20people%20and%20who%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapollopublishers.com%2Findex.php%2Fsingle-at-heart%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESingle%20at%20Heart%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20rise%20in%20solo%20living%20could%20be%20a%20result%20of%20Americans%20delaying%20marriage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMarriage%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20marker%20of%20adulthood%20that%20it%20once%20was.%20Now%20younger%20people%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20feel%20like%20they're%20an%20adult%20if%20they've%20had%20other%20accomplishments%2C%20and%20sometimes%20living%20alone%20is%20one%20of%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20DePaulo%20said.%20%26quot%3BLiving%20alone%20can%20mean%20that%20you%20can%20afford%20to%20do%20so%2C%20and%20that's%20something%20to%20feel%20proud%20of.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20this%20article%2C%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20to%20nine%20millennials%20who%20live%20alone.%20While%20their%20situations%20vary%2C%20they%20all%20said%20that%20living%20alone%20is%20very%20much%20a%20sacrifice%20%E2%80%94%20but%20one%20worth%20making.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20so%2C%20they%20outlined%20the%20promises%20and%20pitfalls%20of%20hitting%20this%20new%20millennial%20milestone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMunday%20acknowledged%20that%20if%20she%20lost%20her%20job%2C%20she'd%20most%20likely%20have%20to%20move%20back%20home%20or%20get%20roommates%2C%20but%20for%20now%2C%20it's%20worth%20the%20risk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20personally%20like%20living%20alone.%20I%20can%20control%20the%20space%2C%20how%20I%20decorate%2C%26quot%3B%20Munday%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20enjoy%20having%20space%20and%20being%20able%20to%20clean%20or%20leave%20it%20messy%20depending%20on%20my%20mood.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jess%20Munday%20outside%20her%20apartment%20building.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664b788c9fc063e829b2d856%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJess%20Munday.%3Cp%3EDara%20Feller%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20singles%20tax%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAria%20Velasquez%2C%2032%2C%20lives%20alone%20in%20her%20one-bedroom%20apartment%20in%20Chicago%2C%20paying%20about%20%241%2C500%20in%20rent%20and%20service%20fees.%20She%20was%20laid%20off%20from%20her%20journalism%20job%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20biggest%20challenge%20is%20taking%20on%20the%20financial%20burden%20alone.%20Her%20partnered%20friends%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20get%20a%20break.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNow%20that%20we're%20in%20our%20early%20to%20mid-30s%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20getting%20married%20or%20partnering%20up%20so%20they're%20moving%20in%20with%20their%20partners%20even%20if%20they're%20not%20married%2C%26quot%3B%20Velasquez%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20will%20cite%20living%20with%20someone%20to%20split%20the%20bills%20with%20as%20a%20benefit%20of%20moving%20in%20with%20someone.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZillow%20recently%20estimated%20that%20people%20living%20alone%20in%20one-bedroom%20rentals%20spent%20over%20%247%2C000%20more%20annually%20on%20housing%20costs%20than%20people%20living%20with%20others%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0a%20difference%20often%20described%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frent-higher-singles-tax-living-alone-new-york-san-francisco-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esingles%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVelasquez%20said%20that%20she%20loves%20living%20alone%20and%20that%20it%20has%20always%20been%20her%20goal.%20She%20values%20privacy%20and%20quiet%20and%20loves%20coming%20home%20to%20nothing%20but%20the%20%26quot%3Bhum%20of%20the%20fridge.%26quot%3B%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20she%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20cost%20of%20many%20items%2C%20including%20groceries%2C%20had%20risen%2C%20adding%20that%20there's%20%26quot%3Bno%20discount%20for%20single-person%20shopping.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20buy%20a%20loaf%20of%20bread%2C%20but%20you%20may%20not%20eat%20the%20entire%20loaf%20in%20a%20short%20period%20of%20time%20because%20maybe%20you%20don't%20want%20a%20sandwich%20every%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Velasquez%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20she's%20able%20to%20rent%20on%20her%20own%2C%20buying%20her%20own%20place%20feels%20like%20a%20distant%20dream%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20view%20it%20the%20same%20way%20people%20think%20about%20winning%20the%20lottery.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMore%20millennials%20living%20with%20Mom%20and%20Dad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EErica%20Charles%2C%2028%2C%20a%20publicist%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20said%20that%20while%20she%20and%20many%20of%20her%20peers%20live%20alone%2C%20others%20had%20moved%20back%20in%20with%20family%20in%20recent%20years.%20She%20said%20she's%20considered%20it%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20could%20save%20%24700%20a%20month%2C%26quot%3B%20Charles%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20could%20go%20toward%20saving%20for%20her%20graduate%20school%20tuition.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20thinking%20about%20how%20I%20can%20scale%20back%20a%20lot.%20I'm%20thinking%20about%20jobs%20that%20pay%20more%20and%20how%20to%20bring%20in%20more%20money%20through%20freelancing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERick%20Fry%2C%20a%20senior%20researcher%20at%20Pew%2C%20said%20the%20share%20of%2018-%20to%2034-year-olds%20living%20in%20their%20families'%20homes%20has%20been%20slowly%20rising%20since%201971%20%26quot%3Band%20particularly%20kind%20of%20picked%20up%20during%20the%20Great%20Recession%2C%26quot%3B%20per%20Pew's%20research.%20As%20of%202023%2C%20he%20said%2C%20it%20was%20about%2032%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20metro%20areas%20that%20have%20the%20highest%20median%20rents%2C%20those%20are%20the%20metro%20areas%20where%20you%20see%20the%20young%20adults%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20living%20with%20Mom%20and%2For%20Dad%2C%26quot%3B%20Fry%20said.%20Per%20BI's%20analysis%20of%20American%20Community%20Survey%20data%20via%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fusa.ipums.org%2Fusa%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIPUMS%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2016%25%20of%20millennials%20lived%20with%20at%20least%20one%20parent%20as%20of%202022.%20(The%20data%20doesn't%20specify%20if%20that%20means%20they're%20living%20with%20their%20parents%20or%20if%20their%20parents%20are%20living%20with%20them.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECharles%20said%20that%20before%20the%20pandemic%2C%20she%20liked%20living%20alone.%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%20it%20was%20a%20rite%20of%20passage%20into%20young%20adulthood%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20Charles%20has%20been%20rethinking%20her%20living%20situation.%20Her%20lease%20is%20ending%20in%20June.%20She%20says%20she's%20been%20laid%20off%20three%20times%20since%202020.%20Because%20of%20finances%2C%20she's%20put%20plans%20to%20pursue%20a%20Ph.D.%20in%20media%20communications%20on%20hold%2C%20and%20she's%20not%20planning%20to%20have%20children%20anytime%20soon.%20She'd%20also%20like%20to%20buy%20a%20house%20in%20the%20next%20three%20years.%20Housing%20prices%20in%20Florida%2C%20where%20she's%20from%2C%20have%20increased%20significantly%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe's%20thought%20about%20whether%20she%20wants%20to%20move%20in%20with%20her%20family%20or%20with%20a%20roommate.%20She's%20been%20cutting%20back%20on%20spending%20and%20has%20been%20doing%20more%20budgeting.%20She's%20even%20taken%20on%20part-time%20food-delivery%20and%20freelancing%20gigs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20a%20privilege%20to%20live%20alone%2C%26quot%3B%20Charles%20said.%20%26quot%3BNow%20it's%20become%20a%20luxury.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESubsidized%20solo%20living%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20lower-earning%20millennials%20are%20able%20to%20get%20assistance%20reaching%20the%20solo-living%20milestone%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20not%20always%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20sitting%20in%20his%20home%20alone%20with%20a%20cat%20on%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664b751920abc1efe8fb8f96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGarak%20Clibborn.%3Cp%3ESydney%20Krantz%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGarak%20Clibborn%2C%2039%2C%20a%20veteran%20in%20California%2C%20has%20been%20homeless%20before.%20He's%20also%20cycled%20through%20at%20least%20eight%20roommates%20while%20renting%20a%20room%20in%20a%20house%20and%20applying%20for%20housing%20assistance%20so%20he%20could%20live%20on%20his%20own.%20After%20waiting%20nearly%20a%20year%2C%20his%20name%20was%20called%20for%20a%20housing%20voucher%2C%20he%20said%20%E2%80%94%20and%20he%20was%20told%20he%20had%2060%20days%20to%20find%20a%20place%20before%20it%20expired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20apartments%20had%20yearslong%20waitlists%2C%20and%20others%20wouldn't%20accept%20vouchers%2C%20which%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhousing-vouchers-crisis-funding-landlords-restrictions-inspections-renters-struggle-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment%20rental%20assistance%3C%2Fa%3E.%20After%20calling%20over%20350%20places%2C%20he%20finally%20found%20a%20spot.%20He's%20been%20living%20alone%20there%20since%202012.%20His%20rent%20just%20went%20up%2C%20to%20over%20%241%2C900.%20With%20his%20subsidy%2C%20he%20pays%20about%20%24380%20a%20month%3B%20he%20uses%20the%20money%20from%20his%20VA%20pension%20to%20help%20cover%20the%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20sitting%20alone%20in%20a%20yard%20%26quot%3Bin%20process%26quot%3B.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664b76189fc063e829b2d52e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGarak%20Clibborn.%3Cp%3ESydney%20Krantz%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEven%20with%20a%20subsidy%2C%20it's%20extraordinarily%20difficult%26quot%3B%20to%20live%20alone%2C%20Clibborn%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20he%20still%20has%20to%20cover%20many%20other%20expenses%20on%20his%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20run%20out%20of%20money%2C%20I'm%20screwed.%20I%20don't%20have%20anything%20to%20help%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWay%20behind%20in%20homeownership%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChaz%20Zimmer%2C%20a%2028-year-old%20who%20sells%20cars%20at%20a%20Subaru%20dealership%2C%20has%20lived%20alone%20in%20his%20apartment%20in%20Waverly%2C%20New%20York%2C%20since%20February%202021.%20He%20pays%20%24550%20a%20month%20in%20rent.%20He%20tried%20to%20purchase%20a%20home%20last%20year%2C%20but%20interest%20rates%20made%20it%20expensive.%20He'd%20eventually%20like%20to%20move%20to%20a%20bigger%20place%2C%20but%20his%20rent%20is%20so%20cheap%20that%20it's%20hard%20to%20justify%20moving%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffiles.stlouisfed.org%2Ffiles%2Fhtdocs%2Fpublications%2Feconomic-synopses%2F2023%2F07%2F28%2Fgenerational-gaps-in-income-and-homeownership.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20analysis%20of%20American%20Community%20Survey%20data%20published%20last%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20non-college-educated%20millennials%20were%20half%20as%20likely%20to%20own%20homes%20at%2030%20as%20non-college-educated%20baby%20boomers%20were%20at%20that%20age.%20It%20also%20found%20that%2038%25%20of%20college-educated%20millennials%20owned%20homes%20at%2030%2C%20less%20than%20the%2054%25%20of%20college-educated%20boomers%20who%20owned%20a%20home%20at%20that%20age.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Portrait%20image%20of%20Chaz%20Zimmer.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664b769820abc1efe8fb9109%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChaz%20Zimmer.%3Cp%3EAdrianna%20Newell%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETomasz%20Piskorski%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20real%20estate%20at%20Columbia%20Business%20School%2C%20said%20it's%20become%20more%20difficult%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20because%20of%20the%20increases%20in%20home%20prices%20and%20interest%20rates%20after%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20millennial%20generation%2C%20it%20could%20take%20years%20to%20catch%20up%20in%20homeownership%2C%26quot%3B%20Piskorski%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZimmer%20hasn't%20given%20up%20hope.%20%26quot%3BSome%20of%20it%20comes%20down%20to%20opportunity%20and%20timing%2C%26quot%3B%20Zimmer%20said.%20He%20works%20on%20commission%2C%20so%20his%20salary%20has%20ranged%20from%20%2462%2C000%20to%20%2479%2C000%20in%20the%20last%20couple%20of%20years.%20He%20said%20he's%20%26quot%3Bfortunate%20to%20have%20a%20pretty%20good%20job%20that%20makes%20a%20decent%20enough%20salary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chaz%20Zimmer%20at%20home.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664b76c720abc1efe8fb9124%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChaz%20Zimmer.%20%3Cp%3EAdrianna%20Newell%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERent%20versus%20a%20mortgage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJames%20Paniagua%2C%2030%2C%20lives%20in%20Oakland%2C%20California.%20Throughout%20college%2C%20he%20lived%20at%20home%20and%20stayed%20there%20until%20right%20before%20the%20pandemic.%20He%20briefly%20lived%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20with%20a%20roommate%2C%20but%20the%20pandemic%20sent%20him%20back%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20essentially%20been%20living%20at%20home%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20my%20twenties%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Last%20year%2C%20he%20decided%20to%20move%20up%20north%20for%20work%20and%20was%20lucky%20enough%20to%20find%20his%20own%20place%20in%20Oakland.%20Before%20making%20that%20move%2C%20a%20few%20financial%20pieces%20had%20to%20fall%20into%20place%3A%20He%20had%20to%20fix%20his%20credit%20score%2C%20and%20he%20needed%20to%20find%20a%20job%20that%20paid%20him%20enough%20to%20move%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20he%20makes%20around%20%24125%2C000%3B%20his%20700-square-foot%20apartment%20with%20a%20parking%20spot%20costs%20him%20around%20%242%2C100%20in%20monthly%20rent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStarting%20to%20pay%20rent%20was%20the%20biggest%20adjustment%2C%20which%20is%20obviously%20a%20huge%20payment%20adjustment%2C%20but%20I%20took%20the%20time%20to%20plan%20out%20that%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20and%20shift%20some%20things%20around%20to%20be%20able%20to%20live%20alone%2C%20but%20still%20live%20the%20lifestyle%20that%20I%20had%20had%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20stopped%20making%20weekly%20mall%20trips%20and%20eats%20at%20home%20more%20regularly%20now.%20He%20said%20he%20likes%20to%20stay%20at%20home%20and%20wants%20to%20make%20his%20space%20as%20cozy%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20he%20said%20he's%20getting%20a%20good%20deal%20for%20what%20he%20has%2C%20some%20older%20adults%20can't%20believe%20how%20much%20he's%20paying%20for%20rent%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey're%20shook.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20more%20than%20some%20of%20my%20relative's%20mortgages%2C%26quot%3B%20Paniagua%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20experience%20of%20living%20alone%20has%20evolved%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20who%20are%20able%20to%20buy%2C%20snagging%20a%20solo%20property%20is%20a%20pivotal%20life%20event%2C%20and%20may%20provide%20comfort%20amid%20the%20uncertainty%20of%20other%20traditional%20milestones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20attending%20graduate%20school%20in%20London%2C%20Julia%20Mazur%2C%20now%2030%2C%20moved%20back%20home%20with%20her%20parents%20for%20two%20years.%20She%20worked%20a%20tech%20job%20that%20paid%20a%20six-figure%20salary%20and%20offered%20a%20generous%20equity%20package%2C%20she%20said.%20At%20age%2025%2C%20she%20saved%20up%20enough%20to%20buy%20her%20own%20condo%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20she%20refinanced%20her%20mortgage%20and%20got%20a%20lower%20rate%3B%20she%20said%20her%20monthly%20costs%20totaled%20about%20%243%2C000.%20Now%20she's%20swapping%20homes%20with%20a%20couple%20in%20Austin%20who%20have%20a%20similarly%20priced%20mortgage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20her%2C%20living%20alone%20is%20empowering.%20She%20said%20she%20thinks%20some%20millennials%20are%20finding%20their%20person%20and%20settling%20down%20while%20others%2C%20including%20her%2C%20are%20finding%20fulfillment%20in%20different%20aspects%20of%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20me%2C%20I%20like%20the%20ability%20to%20move%20around%20and%20to%20travel%2C%20to%20get%20to%20experience%20what%20living%20on%20my%20own%20is%20like%20and%20the%20responsibilities%20that%20come%20with%20it.%20I%20feel%20very%20fulfilled%20by%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20also%20think%20that%20with%20living%20alone%2C%20there%20does%20come%20a%20need%20to%20connect%20with%20humans%20in%20real%20life.%20And%20so%20I%20kind%20of%20make%20myself%20go%20and%20do%20things%20to%20try%20and%20connect%20with%20people%2C%20go%20to%20tennis%20classes%2C%20go%20sit%20up%20alone%20at%20bars%2C%20go%20to%20meetups%20and%20friend%20dates.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDePaulo%20said%20the%20experience%20of%20living%20alone%20has%20changed%20significantly%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years.%20She's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.psychologytoday.com%2Fus%2Fblog%2Fliving-single%2F201905%2Fthe-social-lives-single-people%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20people%20living%20alone%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20connected%20to%20more%20diverse%20people%20%E2%80%94%20and%20more%20people%20overall%20%E2%80%94%20and%20engage%20more%20with%20civic%20life%20and%20community%20institutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELiving%20alone%20is%20worth%20it%20for%20many%2C%20despite%20the%20challenges.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EKathy%20Pierre%2C%2031%2C%20pays%20%241%2C280%20a%20month%20in%20base%20rent%20for%20a%20two-bedroom%20apartment%20in%20Charlotte%2C%20North%20Carolina.%20When%20she%20moved%20to%20Charlotte%2C%20she%20didn't%20know%20anyone%20there%20and%20didn't%20want%20to%20take%20risks%20with%20living%20with%20a%20stranger%20after%20past%20experiences%20with%20roommates.%20%26quot%3BI%20needed%20to%20make%20myself%20afford%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20she%20says%20if%20she%20lived%20with%20family%20or%20a%20roommate%2C%20she'd%20be%20able%20to%20save%20money%20and%20get%20closer%20to%20buying%20a%20home.%20All%20the%20bills%2C%20including%20food%2C%20utilities%2C%20and%20rent%2C%20are%20her%20own%20when%20living%20alone.%20What's%20more%2C%20it%20can%20be%20easy%20not%20to%20talk%20to%20another%20human%20in%20person%20while%20working%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20very%20lovely%20to%20be%20able%20to%20live%20on%20my%20own%20and%20have%20my%20own%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20Pierre%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20to%20negotiate%20with%20other%20people%20about%20what%20happens%20here.%20I%20think%20that%20is%20really%20awesome.%20I%20say%20jokingly%2C%20but%20not%20jokingly%2C%20I%20would%20move%20out%20of%20Charlotte%20before%20I%20look%20for%20a%20roommate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-live-alone-status-symbol-rents-housing-homeownership-expensive-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716624061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664f7a47a961b37edf395345%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-live-alone-status-symbol-rents-housing-homeownership-expensive-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20some%2C%20living%20alone%20has%20become%20the%20new%20millennial%20American%20dream.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan%2CRosalie%20Chan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-li